21) Which tuples could be used in `print("%s %s" % my_tuple)` without causing an error? (Choose all that apply)

Correct

Correct answer
('a', 'b'), (2.0, 3.0)

Explanation
The tuple used in string substitution must have the same number of elements as there are variables in the string. In this case, all tuples with two elements would work.

Further Reading
https://linuxacademy.com/cp/courses/lesson/course/1486/lesson/7/module/158

